Description: Harbour Gates in Annapolis, MD offer spacious studio, 1, 2 and 3 bedroom apartments. We’re at the center of everything you need. Minutes to Route 50, Annapolis Mall and Anne Arundel Medical Center. Only 5 minutes to the Annapolis Towne Centre, Harbour Center, Festival at Riva, downtown historic Annapolis and the City Dock. And in the neighborhood you’ll find unlimited shopping, dining, entertainment, recreation, schools, grocery stores, and many parks. Apartment features include a comfortable living area and separate dining area, glass doors that open to a covered balcony, patio or sunroom with storage closet, large windows with lots of natural light (we provide blinds throughout), ample closet space, central heat & air conditioning and views of landscaped courtyards. Most apartments have full size washer & dryer. We are a pet-friendly apartment and we accept some dogs, all cats and some other types of pets. Utilities are not included in your rent - you pay for electricity and water/sewer. Property features include a relaxing pool with sundeck, indoor heated pool and spa, private showers and locker rooms, fitness center, car wash area, racquetball court, recycling areas, mail delivery in each building, on-site management and 24-hour emergency maintenance. For more information and availability, visit www.harbourgatesapartments.com.

Description:
Fully furnished, renovated 2 bedroom, 1.5 bath apartment in West Annapolis on Annapolis Street, less than 500 yards from the Naval Academy. One mile to center of downtown. This apartment is located on the second floor in the rear of the building. Parking included. 
Fully stocked kitchen, two flat screen tvs, washer/dryer, all furnished. Twin over full in one bedroom and a queen bed in the other. Steam shower with oversized jetted tub. Walk to cafes, restaurants, grocery store, Rite Aid, 7Eleven and more. Jump on route 50 in 2 mins from this quiet secluded neighborhood.

Description: As the GOLD recipient of the Active Adult Community Award from Maryland Multi-Housing Association, Gardens of Annapolis is the premier senior living community in Annapolis, MD. Just moments from Annapolis Mall and the Annapolis Town Center, you can enjoy and appreciate all the comforts of independent living at this luxurious rental community created exclusively for seniors 62 and better. Celebrate the retirement you have worked hard for in Anne Arundel County. Close to the shopping, restaurants and social activities that you are used to and yet still a part of a welcoming and diverse community, the Gardens of Annapolis provides you with the resources to relax and live your life to the fullest! As a resident of a Cove Property Management community, you will experience courteous and capable service as we strive to exceed your expectations every time.

Kitchen:

* Microwave

Too much to list a must see.

(410) 268-8400 - Admiral's Reach Second Floor Condo - 2 Master Suites. - 607 ADMIRAL’S REACH -#201
Large and spacious Admirals Reach's 2BA / 2BR corner end unit with extra windows. There are 2 master suites in this unit, each with a private bath and plenty of closet space, both bedrooms are a very generously sized. Centrally located for easy access to Route 50 or downtown.

Including a living room/dining room combination, 1 bedroom, full kitchen and a separate office/den. There are lovely views of the city in each room of this home! Being right in the heart of Annapolis, you're walking distance to all that Downtown has to offer! Fine dining, local eateries, and boutiques! Less than 2 miles from Route 50 making for an easy daily commute! This home will be available July 15! Contact us by submitting an inquiry!

---- SCHEDULE A SHOWING ONLINE AT: http://showmojo.com/lac/3987198085 ----
Great 2 bedroom+study, 1.5 bath end unit town home in the water privileged Dreams Landing community of Annapolis, located on the Severn river. Three level home: Main level consists of a living area with hardwood floors and built in shelving; eat in kitchen and powder / laundry room. Two bedrooms + full bath on the second floor. Loft study area on the third. Fully fenced back patio area with direct access to communal area.
Community facilities include a pool, patio and marina all with superb water views. For small additional fee residents can have access to: a boat slip in the marina, work-out room, kayak storage and woodworking shop.

This two-level condo in excellent condition can be your new home! It is close to shopping, downtown Annapolis, and accessible to DC. It includes a large back decking facing onto a wooded undeveloped hillside below. It has tall ceilings and lots of natural light. It boasts an exterior storage unit and is located in a pleasant neighborhood with reserved off-street parking. Kitchen includes an island, and all appliances. New water heater, washer and dryer are included.
Rental Terms: Rent: $1,900, Application Fee: $45, Security Deposit: $1,900, Available Now
Pet Policy: Cats not allowed, Dogs not allowed
This property allows self guided viewing without an appointment. Contact for details.

Description:
This classic mid-century Eastport cottage with water access to Back Creek has been stylishly remodeled to double the space, the sunlight, and the charm. Vintage pine floors glow amid period molding. The living room has been bumped out into a sun room large enough to warm a family's daily dinette; the old kitchen has had a hip rehab (think soapstone, not granite); the French doors of dining room (or maybe family room?) let out onto large yard framed by nativist landscaping. Original first floor bedroom is well sized, but needs an armoire; it has first floor full bath to itself.
Now up to the 2nd floor dormer addition: stairwell opens onto cozy sunlit nook; corridor leads to master loft, with his-'n-her closets; the master bedroom shares a full bath with kid bedroom (or office) through jack-'n-jill doors.
The Basement houses laundry and lots of storage space. Outdoors, expansive fenced-in yard includes stone patio for barbecue and lawn large enough for dog-runs, full-field T-ball, internecine volley ball, or competitive croquet.
Meander with the dog through Parkwood down to the community association's beach and piers on Back Creek. Or else head around the corner to the Eastport shopping mall -- to the Annapolis Gym for a work-out or rub-down; to Palate Pleasers for gourmet take-out & baked goods; to the Eastport Farmer's Market for garden-fresh fruits &amp; vegetables; to Eastport Kitchen for gourmet sadwiches; to Eastport Liquors for in-store specials on wines and liquors. Or hop over to Vin 909 across Bay Ridge for the popular wine-bar and small-plates, or saunter down Chesapeake Ave to Bakers & Co. for buttery bread and pastries; then continue down to 6th St. and over the Annapolis harbor scene to City Dock. Nice way to live.
For an appointment to view, call Jason or Liz at 443-699-5438. Minimum lease is 6 months. Available October 1st. $2700.00/mo, $2700.00 security deposit. This property is managed by a responsible landlord using Rentalutions landlord software.

Description: Apply by August 13th to enjoy waived application fees and a $200 gift card to Cooper's Hawk. Crosswinds at Annapolis Towne Centre is a brand new apartment community with upscale apartment finishes and exquisite amenity spaces you won't find anywhere else. Vibrant, urban and just minutes from historic downtown Annapolis, Crosswinds is redefining traditional luxury living. The best shopping, dining and entertainment, a happening social life, elegantly styled apartments-you'll find it all right here. With easy access to Baltimore and DC, there's never been a more convenient place to call home. Our leasing office is now open so stop by today. We are located directly next door to Paladar at 1903 Towne Centre Boulevard.

Residents will not only enjoy up to date homes, but gorgeous landscaping, a playground, and plenty of space to gather together as a community.

Description: Homes at the Glen is a thriving townhome community, where 56 families call home. This beautiful, pet-friendly community operates under a lease to purchase program. The townhomes have three stories with one, two, or three bedrooms. All homes have washers and dryers, wall-to-wall carpeting, and dishwashers; some of the townhomes offer garages as well. You can enjoy quality social time with your children in our community room or on the playground. The community center offers a business center and after school homework club. For your convenience, Homes at the Glen is located near shopping centers, public transportation, and schools. On-site maintenance is also provided to give you peace of mind in your new home. Homes at the Glen is a Homes for America community.

Description: Welcome to North Severn Village! North Severn Village is located near the entrance of NSA Annapolis and just moments away from the from historic downtown Annapolis waterfront. North Severn Village features spacious two-story, three-, and four-bedroom homes, all of which feature fenced in backyards and storage sheds. Neighborhood amenities include two pools with adjacent snack shops, several tot-lots, and landscaped playgrounds. There are a wide variety of shops and services at the entrance of NSA Annapolis, and North Severn Village’s proximity to downtown Annapolis assures easy access to the restaurants and fine shops along the waterfront. The nearby Annapolis Mall and the shopping centers along Route 2 offer plenty of opportunities for shopping, recreation, and dining. There is a wide selection of K-12 schools in the surrounding area. There is a two-pet maximum for either cats or dogs. For more information regarding breed and other restrictions, please contact the Lincoln Military Housing District Office. No pet deposits and no monthly pet fees are required.
